    "b-render-intro-2": {
      "id": "b-render-intro-2",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The render layer is the presentation side of the canvas engine: given an "
        },
        {
          "insert": "InteractiveCanvasDocument",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/state/schema/document.ts",
              "symbol": "InteractiveCanvasDocument"
            },
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " and a viewport, it draws objects, connections, sections, and annotations to the screen as a world-space DOM/SVG tree. It owns no editing state of its own — it is the shared renderer both the read-only viewer and the interactive editor mount, driven entirely by props."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-render-heading-canvasstage-3": {
      "id": "b-render-heading-canvasstage-3",
      "flavour": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "CanvasStage"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-render-canvasstage-body-4": {
      "id": "b-render-canvasstage-body-4",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "CanvasStage",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/render/CanvasStage.tsx",
              "symbol": "CanvasStage"
            },
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " is the top-level exported component (a large, ~1800-line file). It takes the document, the viewport (pan/zoom), selection and interaction state, and a couple of slot props ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "overlay",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " for screen-space UI, "
        },
        {
          "insert": "worldOverlay",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " for things like the inline connector-label editor input the editor injects) and renders the whole scene. It applies the camera transform — translate by "
        },
        {
          "insert": "-viewport.x * zoom, -viewport.y * zoom",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " then scale by "
        },
        {
          "insert": "zoom",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — to a single world layer, and projects world coordinates to screen coordinates via "
        },
        {
          "insert": "worldToScreen",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " for every screen-space overlay (marquee, snap guides, distribution guides, selection handles)."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-render-canvasstage-helpers-5": {
      "id": "b-render-canvasstage-helpers-5",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Structurally it is one large render tree assembled from many small, single-purpose sub-renderers rather than one deeply nested component. Notable pieces: "
        },
        {
          "insert": "ObjectShape",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/render/ObjectShape.tsx",
              "symbol": "ObjectShape"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (also exported) is a thin registry dispatcher since the def conversion — it resolves the object's registered ObjectDef via "
        },
        {
          "insert": "objectDefFor",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/objects/object-def.ts",
              "symbol": "objectDefFor"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "section",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " by type, everything else by effective render shape) and renders "
        },
        {
          "insert": "def.render",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "; its generic fallback only fires for a render shape with no registered def. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "Connector",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " draws one routed connector (hit path, visible path, arrowhead markers, dashed styles, bend-affordance stubs, endpoint handles), paired with "
        },
        {
          "insert": "ConnectionLabelChip",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " and "
        },
        {
          "insert": "ConnectorDragPreview",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "; "
        },
        {
          "insert": "SelectionBox",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (also exported) draws the screen-space selection outline and resize handles; "
        },
        {
          "insert": "AnchorDots",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/render/overlays/AnchorDots.tsx",
              "symbol": "AnchorDots"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " draws the FigJam-style connection anchor dots on selected objects at the def-derived anchor positions, visibility-gated below "
        },
        {
          "insert": "ANCHOR_DOTS_MIN_ZOOM",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (0.5 — the dots stay grabbable at opacity 0); "
        },
        {
          "insert": "Marquee",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", "
        },
        {
          "insert": "PlacePreview",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", "
        },
        {
          "insert": "SnapGuideLine",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", "
        },
        {
          "insert": "DistributionGuideLine",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", and "
        },
        {
          "insert": "SpacingChips",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " render selection-rectangle, tool-placement ghost, and alignment/distribution guide overlays. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "renderOrderedObjects",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " computes the geometric layer-cake order before the scene is drawn: sections first by containment depth, then area descending, then stable schema index; non-sections keep schema order. See "
        },
        {
          "insert": "canvas-10-system-design-30-layering",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "10-system-design/30-layering",
              "label": "canvas-10-system-design-30-layering"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " for the full model."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-render-canvasstage-imports-6": {
      "id": "b-render-canvasstage-imports-6",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "CanvasStage composes the other render-layer modules directly: it calls "
        },
        {
          "insert": "gridBackground",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " once per render to compute the dot-grid CSS background for the stage's root div, and it pulls "
        },
        {
          "insert": "canvasSurfaceStyle",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/theme.ts",
              "symbol": "canvasSurfaceStyle"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " from theme.ts for the grid/guide/highlight CSS variables. What it deliberately no longer does is resolve object colors or carry per-shape CSS: each object's colors resolve inside its def via "
        },
        {
          "insert": "resolveObjectRoleColors",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/objects/object-chrome.tsx",
              "symbol": "resolveObjectRoleColors"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (palette.ts role tables), and the stage's embedded style tag is composed as a shared base block plus "
        },
        {
          "insert": "OBJECT_DEFS_CSS",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/objects/object-def.ts",
              "symbol": "OBJECT_DEFS_CSS"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — the concatenated "
        },
        {
          "insert": "css",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " of every registered def. Code blocks tokenize their own "
        },
        {
          "insert": "text",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " inside the code-block def ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "objects/code-block/def.tsx",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " calling "
        },
        {
          "insert": "tokenizeCodeBlock",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " from render/code-tokenizer.ts). The board background stays a fixed light surface ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "#F5F5F5",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
