      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "code-tokenizer.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " is a small, deliberately non-general syntax highlighter used only to render the in-canvas "
        },
        {
          "insert": "code-block",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " object shape (not related to the docs system's own "
        },
        {
          "insert": "code",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " block flavour). Its own header comment is explicit that it is \"intentionally NOT a real syntax-highlighting engine\" — no grammar, no AST, no language server — just regex rules tuned for the two languages the FigJam reference boards actually show. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "tokenizeCodeLine",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/render/code-tokenizer.ts",
              "symbol": "tokenizeCodeLine"
            },
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " dispatches on a language tag: for "
        },
        {
          "insert": "\"python\"",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " it recognizes comments, strings, a fixed keyword set, and capitalized identifiers (rendered as \"type\" color, mimicking class/type-name highlighting); for "
        },
        {
          "insert": "\"json\"",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " it splits quoted-string spans from plain spans, coloring a quoted string followed by a colon as a key (\"type\" color) versus a value (\"string\" color), and recognizing "
        },
        {
          "insert": "true",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": "false",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": "null",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " as keywords. Any other language falls back to untokenized plain text in the base foreground color. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "tokenizeCodeBlock",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/render/code-tokenizer.ts",
              "symbol": "tokenizeCodeBlock"
            },
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (the function CanvasStage calls) splits a full code-block body on newlines and tokenizes each line independently. The tokenizer's core invariant — enforced by its test suite — is that concatenating a line's output tokens reproduces the original line exactly; it must never drop or reorder characters."
        }
